<br>
I also agree that there needs to be more &quot;tough roads&quot; for clerics in getting their epic.  Like he states, clerics ALWAYS have people to help them on their epic.  The reasoning behind this is that everyone benefits from a cleric with a clicky. While this is true, a guild also benefits from EVERY class that has their epic.  The more epic weilders you have the more damage you are doing and it is more likely that you will have fewer deaths that the clerics will have to click. <br>
<br>
The door goes both ways, we just need to learn to look at the hinges.<br>
<br>
Take the mage for example.  Most don't consider that a guild friendly epic.  The mage epic is a spell.  It is always on the mage even during cr's.  This also means that he can cast a pet without the use of components.  So, with a mage that already deals huge amounts of damage, you now have a massive pet.  A pet that pretty much buffs himself, cast some nasty damage spells, has a DS that does I think 50 damage,  and he has somewhere around 3k in hitpoints.  <br>
<br>
Granted, you don't rush out and fine every epic mage you can, but you should appreciate each member of your guild. <br>
<br>
